HOUSE BILL No. 1389
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 31-9-2; IC 31-10-3.5; IC 34-11-2-17.1.
Synopsis: Adoption and foster care matters. Prohibits a governmental
entity from discriminating against a person in adoption and foster care
matters based on the person's sincerely held religious belief. Allows a
person to bring a cause of action against a governmental entity for
discriminating against the person, or raise a violation as a claim or
defense in a judicial proceeding, and allows for certain remedies.
Provides that there is a two year statute of limitation for a
discrimination claim.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Lindauer
January 8, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Judiciary.
