17 SECTION 6. IC 31-10-3.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
18 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
19 JULY 1, 2026]:
20 Chapter 3.5. Antidiscrimination in Adoption and Foster
21 Proceedings
22 Sec. 1. (a) Except as provided in subsection (b), a governmental
23 entity may not discriminate against any of the following:
24 (1) A person that provides, or declines to provide, an adoption
25 or foster care service in a manner consistent with the person's
26 sincerely held religious belief.
27 (2) An adoptive parent (as defined in IC 31-9-2-6) who raises,
28 or intends to raise, a child in a manner consistent with the
29 adoptive parent's sincerely held religious belief.
30 (3) A foster parent (as defined in IC 31-9-2-47) who raises, or
31 intends to raise, a child in a manner consistent with the foster
32 parent's sincerely held religious belief.
33 (4) A person that in a matter concerning adoption or foster
34 care service:
35 (A) maintains any policy and procedure; or
36 (B) otherwise acts;
37 consistent with the person's sincerely held religious belief.
38 (b) A governmental entity may consider whether a person
39 described in subsection (a) shares the same religion or faith
40 tradition as a child when considering placement of the child to
41 prioritize the child's placement with a person of the same religion
42 or faith tradition.
